      "date": "2020-03-09 18:17:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis looks correct, though I don't normally think of swapping a lock for a memory barrier as a simplification...  But in this case, the lock is only (well, only usefully) acting as a memory barrier anyway, because it's not being used for atomicity.  Interesting.  Thanks for the writeup, Neil.",
